<font color="#FF0000">I STAND IN YOUR SHADOW</font><br>
<tt>Wed Aug 13 22:01:30 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Ed,<br><br>
Sorry about not getting back to you sooner, but I couldn't find the words.  I am honored that you share your deepest secrets with me.  I know the gang all reads these posts, but I felt a personal connection as if only we were aware of the lines.<br><br>
You are wrong about having no words to express your love.  The fact that you share with me the moment of your rebirth is something I will never forget.  Warriors trust when they tell their stories and I will remember that such trust is sacred, never to be broken.  We are bound my brother by our sharing.  I will defend your honor and the sanctity of this experience.  You are my wingman to whom I trust my life.<br><br>
I am humbled in the shadow of your experience.  I was spared the pain of the slow death.  Mine was swift and sure and spared me all the motion.  I am now aware that God was merciful.  I do not know if I possess the strength you have shown.  My memories serve me well about the path we have shared and the hell that occured below angels one.  I am positive without a doubt you were the greatest aviator on earth.  2 years and three months in a helo in combat is an accomplishment that any aviator can brag about.  I would be honored to share those memories.<br><br>
I am sure at times that the years of living at the edge were only possible because I was numb, but we sure were cocky bastards weren't we.  I flew there for 27 years and always chose the high risk jobs.  Grand father before I quite.<br><br>
I learned to like the solitude and the conflict.  I still like it today.  I have always felt comfort in knowing that I was untouchable and at the same time new I was missing all the things which emotions allow.<br><br>
Mustang Two Four, take my hand and we will walk this path together and close the circle.
<p><code>--   (Silent Warrior) </code><p>


